column22: There was no run-off needed because Foster won over 50% of the vote.
Incumbent Agnus King, an Independent candidate, received 246,772 votes (58.6% of the total vote) and won the election.; The other vote was: Scattered Write-Ins (Other) 44,015
The other vote was: Humphrey, Hubert Horatio III (Democrat Farmer-Labor) 587,060; Scattered Write-Ins (Other) 13,175
The other vote was: Scattered Write-Ins (Other) 33,802
